  "local_port": 52326,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good young hard rock artist similar to bands like Rage Against The Machine, Wakrat, Foo Fighters, Downset, ACDC and Xombie etc?",
  "response": "If you're looking for young hard rock artists or bands with a similar vibe to Rage Against the Machine, Wakrat, Foo Fighters, Downset, AC/DC, and Xombie, here\u2019s a mix of up-and-coming and slightly more established acts that carry the torch for high-energy, riff-driven, and socially conscious rock:\n\n---\n\n### **Similar to Rage Against the Machine/Wakrat (Fusion of Punk, Rap, and Rock):**\n1. **FEVER 333**  \n   - A politically charged, high-energy band blending rap, punk, and rock. Jason Aalon Butler (ex-letlive.) leads this explosive group.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"Burn It\"* or *\"Made An America.\"*\n\n2. **Zheani**  \n   - Australian songwriter and rapper with a raw, rebellious edge and industrial-rock influences.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"The Question.\"*\n\n3. **Bob Vylan**  \n   - UK duo combining punk, grime, and hard rock with biting social commentary.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"We Live Here\"* or *\"GDP.\"*\n\n4. **The Chats**  \n   - More punk-driven, but their raw energy and rebellious spirit resonate with RATM's ethos.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"Smoko\"* or *\"Pub Feed.\"*\n\n---\n\n### **Similar to Foo Fighters (Melodic Hard Rock):**\n1. **The Dirty Nil**  \n   - Canadian band with a mix of punk energy and melodic hard rock riffs.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"Doom Boy\"* or *\"That\u2019s What Heaven Feels Like.\"*\n\n2. **Des Rocs**  \n   - A solo artist with a bluesy, energetic rock style reminiscent of Foo Fighters.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"Let Me Live / Let Me Die\"* or *\"Used to the Darkness.\"*\n\n3. **Cleopatrick**  \n   - A two-piece band with a raw, riff-heavy sound and a modern edge.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"Hometown\"* or *\"The Drake.\"*\n\n---\n\n### **Similar to Downset (Rap-Metal/Hardcore):**\n1. **UnityTX**  \n   - A modern rap-metal band blending hardcore, hip-hop, and heavy riffs.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"Madness\"* or *\"Ruckus.\"*\n\n2. **Renounced**  \n   - UK hardcore band with metallic riffs and intense energy.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"The Realist,\"* though they\u2019re more hardcore than rap-metal.\n\n3. **BackWordz**  \n   - Rap-metal with a libertarian slant and crushing grooves.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"Self Ownership\"* or *\"Poetic Justice.\"*\n\n---\n\n### **Similar to AC/DC (Classic Hard Rock/Blues Rock):**\n1. **Airbourne**  \n   - Australian rockers who are essentially AC/DC 2.0, with high-octane riffs and energy.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"Runnin\u2019 Wild\"* or *\"Live It Up.\"*\n\n2. **Greta Van Fleet**  \n   - A newer band with a classic rock sound inspired by Led Zeppelin and AC/DC.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"Highway Tune\"* or *\"Safari Song.\"*\n\n3. **The Sheepdogs**  \n   - A retro-rock band with a bluesy, hard rock edge.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"I Don\u2019t Know\"* or *\"Feeling Good.\"*\n\n---\n\n### **Similar to Xombie (Alternative Metal/Rock):**\n1. **Turnstile**  \n   - A hardcore band that\u2019s evolved into a more eclectic, alternative rock/metal sound.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"HOLIDAY\"* or *\"Mystery.\"*\n\n2. **Code Orange**  \n   - A genre-bending band blending hardcore, metal, and industrial rock.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"Swallowing the Rabbit Whole\"* or *\"Underneath.\"*\n\n3. **Ho99o9**  \n   - A chaotic blend of punk, hip-hop, and industrial rock.  \n   - **Check out:** *\"War Is Hell\"* or *\"Bone Collector.\"*\n\n---\n\n### **Other Recommendations:**\n- **Puppy** (UK band with grunge and hard rock influences)  \n- **Royal Blood** (Two-piece band with heavy riffs and a modern edge)  \n- **The Glorious Sons** (Canadian rock with a raw, anthemic sound)  \n- **Dead Poet Society** (Alternative rock with a dark, heavy edge)  \n\nThese artists and bands should give you a fresh, modern take on the hard rock sound you\u2019re looking for while staying true to the spirit of the legends you love!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
